/* A small numeric PC (e.g. `5`) still routes through the script-fn
 * dispatch path because the C-level VM API uses bare numbers as
 * function entries; see source/vm/vm.c:OP_CALL.  The PC range check
 * catches obviously-bad values like this one.  Fully fixing the
 * conflation between user numbers and function-PC numbers requires a
 * dedicated value tag and is tracked separately. */
VAR x = 9999999;
x(1, 2);
